#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:1
msgid "Modules and Crates"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:3
msgid "Default to the narrowest visibility (`narrow-visibility`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:5
msgid ""
"Start private, then widen to `pub(super)`, `pub(crate)`, or `pub` only when "
"an actual external consumer requires it."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:10
msgid "// Good — restricted to the parent module\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:15
msgid "// ...\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:17
msgid "// Bad — unnecessarily wide\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:22
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2951](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2951) and "
"[\\#2605](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/"
"pull/2605#discussion_r2720506912)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:26
msgid "Qualify function calls with the parent module (`qualified-fn-imports`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:28
msgid ""
"When importing a free function or a static/constant from another module, "
"import the **parent module** and access the item through it (`module::"
"function()`, `module::CONSTANT`). Do not import free functions or statics "
"directly by name."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:34
msgid ""
"This convention is recommended by [_The Rust Programming Language_](https://"
"doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch07-04-bringing-paths-into-scope-with-the-use-"
"keyword.html) and followed by the Rust compiler codebase. It serves two "
"purposes:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:39
msgid ""
"The call site makes it clear that an imported item is being used, not a "
"local one."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:42
msgid "The module name provides context that complements the item name."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:46
msgid "// Good — module-qualified function call\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:50
msgid "// Good — module-qualified static access\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:55
msgid "// Bad — bare function name; unclear origin at call site\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:60
msgid "// Bad — bare static name; could be mistaken for a local constant\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:67
msgid ""
"This rule applies to **free functions and statics/constants**. Types, "
"traits, and enum variants should still be imported directly by name, "
"following the standard Rust convention."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:72
msgid "Use workspace dependencies (`workspace-deps`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:74
msgid ""
"Always declare shared dependencies in the workspace `[workspace."
"dependencies]` table and reference them with `.workspace = true` in member "
"crates."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/modules-and-crates.md:79
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"# In the workspace root Cargo.toml\n"
"[workspace.dependencies]\n"
"ostd = { version = \"0.17.0\", path = \"ostd\" }\n"
"bitflags = \"2.6\"\n"
"\n"
"# In a member crate's Cargo.toml\n"
"[dependencies]\n"
"ostd.workspace = true\n"
"bitflags.workspace = true\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
